snippet.title: I Let My Subscribers Pick My First Tattoo
snippet.description:
I've never gotten a tattoo, so I decided to take the plunge...and as a celebration for 5 million subscribers, I wanted to let you guys help me choose my very first tattoo! So I had you submit suggestions, and then I picked 4 options and had you all vote on YouTube, and then went to a parlor and got ~tatted~!

A big thank you once again to Kimmy, you can find her here!!
https://www.instagram.com/kimmytanofficial/
https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCd1sedYHrN-xklnomUu1btA

And thanks again to Skin Deep LA for allowing us to film!

snippet.textDisplay:
I've been using the DIVA cup for a few months now and I love it!

I find that the cup really helps with cramping. I was also having pain putting in the M size cup so I switched to the smallest cup. I have to keep a good eye on it during heavy flow but it's so much easier to take out and put in.

Tips:
If you are having issues grabbing the stem to pull out, push it out with your pelvic muscles like a babeh.

If twisting it is difficult after inserting, you can pull it out slightly. For me, this opens up the cup fully.

snippet.textDisplay:
I've menstrual cup (in Finland, the most popular menstrual cup brand is "lunette").
I absolutely love mine! I had to practice first how to get that in, but...after several tryings, I got it!
But when I was suppose to got it out... it was one frustrating time, and I almost started to panic :D I already knew that it would come sooner or later, since the little air holes would be covered in blood (so, it wouldn't be holding there no longer).
And I don't know about you, but Lunette says that DO NOT pull the cup out of your vagina by the little stem, because it will make things A LOT WORSE! So you've to grap it by the same way as you put it in (like grap it with your fingers and fold it).
